===Etymology 1===
Originally a [[Sussex]] habitational name, the word "[[leag]]" or "[[ley]]" meaning [[field]] in [[Anglo-Saxon]]. Hence, "bent field", see also {{mention|en|Bentham}}.

====Proper noun====
